# Test API keys for gated live-LLM integration tests.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.test` (gitignored) and fill in real keys, OR export
# these vars in your shell. Without them, gated live-API tests SKIP cleanly and
# the rest of the suite runs normally — they never fail for a missing key.
#
# `npm run capture-live-api-keys -- --apply` merges into `.env.test` (never
# deletes). It manages only the four TEST_* keys listed below; anything else you
# add (e.g. TEST_ELEVENLABS_API_KEY for E2E) is preserved across refreshes.
#
# `.env.test` is loaded into process.env by vitest.setup.ts (dotenv, override:false,
# so shell/CI vars take precedence). See docs/plans/improve_tests.md §4.
#
# Cheapest models are preferred for live tests:
#   - DeepSeek V4 Flash via OpenRouter: model id `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` (~$1e-5/call)
#   - Claude Haiku:                     model id `claude-haiku-4-5`
#
# Where to get keys: your Rebel desktop app settings (Settings → providers), or
# the provider dashboards (openrouter.ai / console.anthropic.com).

# OpenRouter key — unlocks DeepSeek and other models (preferred for cheap live tests).
TEST_OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# Direct Anthropic API key (sk-ant-...). Used for Haiku live tests and cloud-continuity live mode.
TEST_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# OpenAI key (sk-...) — used by the OpenAI Chat-Completions live proxy test.
TEST_OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Legacy name some existing integration tests read (cloud-service / cloud-client).
# Set to the same value as TEST_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY if you use those suites.
TEST_CLAUDE_API_KEY=

# NOTE — ChatGPT Pro (Codex subscription) live test needs NO key here.
# Its OAuth tokens are safeStorage-encrypted on disk, so they can't live in
# .env.test. The codexSubscription live cell instead reads your DESKTOP login
# (sign in via Settings → providers → ChatGPT Pro) and decrypts it read-only via
# Electron at test time; it skips cleanly if you haven't signed in. Nothing to set.
